  You may charge any price or no price for each copy that you distribute,
and may offer protection or support for a fee.

  3. Network Interaction.

  If you modify the Program, your modified version must prominently offer
all users interacting with it remotely through a computer network
(accessed through the same server that runs the modified version) the
opportunity to receive the corresponding source code for their version.

  This requirement applies to the modified version if it is a network-based
service, regardless of whether it is a modification of the original
Program.

  4. Copying.

  You may copy and distribute the Program (or a work based on it) in
object code or source code form, under the terms of sections 1 and 2,
provided that you also meet each of these conditions:

    a) Accompany the object code form with the complete corresponding
    source code, or use a written offer valid for at least three years
    to provide the source code.

    b) The source code must be provided under this License.

    c) Installation information must be provided if the object code form
    is used in user products.

  5. Combining and Distributing.

  You may convey a covered work under terms of your choice, if you meet
all conditions of this License. Your network interactions are not
affected by this choice.

  6. Conveying Non-Source Forms.

  You may convey a covered work in object code form under this License,
provided that you also meet the conditions of sections 1 and 2.

  You may install and run a modified version in a user product without
conveying it, if you meet all conditions of this License.

  7. Additional Terms.

  Additional permissions that are reasonable under the circumstances may
be added to a copy. You may offer additional or different warranty
protection and support for a fee.

  8. Termination.

  You may not propagate or modify a covered work except as expressly
provided under this License. Any attempt otherwise to propagate or
modify it is void, and will automatically terminate your rights under
this License.

  9. Acceptance.

  You need not accept this License in order to install, propagate, or
distribute a Program, nor any derivative works. However, no one else
may grant you permission to do so under terms other than this License.

                     NO WARRANTY

  10. Because the program is licensed free of charge, there is no
warranty for the program, to the extent permitted by applicable law.

  11. If the program is modified by someone else and passed on, you
